Description: I am selling my genuine Fender Standard Telecaster made in 2008 in the Mexican factory. The guitar is in Excellent condition. 6 string, right handed, serial number MZ0244546, solid body, dramatic mother-of-pearl pick guard on black gloss body. Includes Deluxe Electrical Guitar Hard shell Case. Please see all pictures.All original parts and nothing needs repair. The original neck is nice and straight with the action set med/low. Almost no fret wear. Beautiful condition with practically no play wear. Features the best of the old and the new: a fast-action maple neck, cast/sealed Fender machine heads, two classic single-coil pickups, and a 3-barrel string-thru-body bridge with 3 brass saddles. The bridge, saddles, tuners, and bridge pickup (basically all the metal parts) are clean with no corrosion.Input jacks, volume & tone control knobs are in great shape. Electronics are in fine working order, so it's ready to go! The guitar sounds and plays awesome. Cosmetically the guitar has had a few bumps but all of this is purely cosmetic and doesn't affect the playability of the guitar at all.
